Get Running in 2 Minutes
Prerequisites
Node.js 18+ installed
npm or yarn
Installation
# 1. Navigate to project directory
cd docandgo-marketing

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Start development server
npm run dev
Visit http://localhost:3000 - Your site is live! ğŸ‰
What You'll See
âœ… Fully functional marketing website with:
Responsive design (mobile, tablet, desktop)
Smooth animations and interactions
Email signup form with success state
Interactive feature cards
Auto-rotating testimonials
Complete footer with navigation
Making Changes
Update Content
All content is in app/page.tsx:
// Line ~26: Change features
const features = [
  {
    title: 'Your Title',
    description: 'Your description',
    icon: 'ğŸ¯',
    stat: 'Your stat'
  },
  // ... more features
];

// Line ~47: Change testimonials
const testimonials = [
  {
    quote: "Your testimonial",
    author: "Name",
    role: "Role"
  },
  // ... more testimonials
];
Change Colors
Search for these hex codes in app/page.tsx and replace:
#0f766e - Primary teal (buttons, accents)
#14b8a6 - Secondary teal (gradients)
#fafaf9 - Background off-white
#1a1a1a - Text black
Change Fonts
In app/page.tsx, find the Google Fonts import (~line 62):
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=YOUR_FONT&display=swap');
Deploy to Production
Option 1: Vercel (Easiest)
npm i -g vercel
vercel
Option 2: Netlify
npm run build
# Upload .next folder to Netlify
Option 3: Traditional Hosting
npm run build
npm start
# Set up reverse proxy to port 3000
Connect Email Form
The form currently shows a success message but doesn't send data.
To connect it to your backend:
Open app/page.tsx
Find the handleSubmit function (~line 20)
Replace with:
const handleSubmit = async (e: React.FormEvent) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  
  try {
    const response = await fetch('/api/signup', {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
      body: JSON.stringify({ email })
    });
    
    if (response.ok) {
      setSubmitted(true);
      setEmail('');
    }
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Signup failed:', error);
  }
};
Create API route at app/api/signup/route.ts
